rComments: His class was very slow and was carried away by too many sources which dragged the class down with it. We just ended on the 28th, and we had to skip 3 weeks of course material because he kept talking about things we already discussed the week before. A lot of his journal and test questions were opinion based and subject to tough responses.

Probably the worst prof at UTSC. Aside from the fact that he grades insanely hard, he usually tests material that he never taught in class. As a matter of fact, he claims that certain material will not be on his midterms or finals and then pull a complete 180 - without telling the class - and test that the material anyway; he's not honest.
